53  * Startup file for gcc has been updated according to CMSIS 3.2.
54  * System initialization updated.
55  * MCG - registers updated.
56  * PORTA, PORTB, PORTC, PORTE - registers for digital filter removed.
57  * - rev. 2.1 (2013-10-30)
58  * Definition of BITBAND macros updated to support peripherals with 32-bit acces disabled.
59  * - rev. 2.2 (2013-12-09)
60  * DMA - EARS register removed.
61  * AIPS0, AIPS1 - MPRA register updated.
62  * - rev. 2.3 (2014-01-24)
63  * Update according to reference manual rev. 2
64  * ENET, MCG, MCM, SIM, USB - registers updated
65  * - rev. 2.4 (2014-02-10)
66  * The declaration of clock configurations has been moved to separate header file system_MK64F12.h
67  * Update of SystemInit() and SystemCoreClockUpdate() functions.
68  * - rev. 2.5 (2014-02-10)
69  * The declaration of clock configurations has been moved to separate header file system_MK64F12.h
70  * Update of SystemInit() and SystemCoreClockUpdate() functions.
71  * Module access macro module_BASES replaced by module_BASE_PTRS.
72  * - rev. 2.6 (2014-08-28)
73  * Update of system files - default clock configuration changed.
74  * Update of startup files - possibility to override DefaultISR added.
75  * - rev. 2.7 (2014-10-14)
76  * Interrupt INT_LPTimer renamed to INT_LPTMR0, interrupt INT_Watchdog renamed to INT_WDOG_EWM.
77  * - rev. 2.8 (2015-02-19)
78  * Renamed interrupt vector LLW to LLWU.
79  *
80  * ###################################################################
81  */

94 /*
95  * MK64F12 ADC
96  *
97  * Analog-to-Digital Converter
98  *
99  * Registers defined in this header file:
100  * - ADC_SC1 - ADC Status and Control Registers 1
101  * - ADC_CFG1 - ADC Configuration Register 1
102  * - ADC_CFG2 - ADC Configuration Register 2
103  * - ADC_R - ADC Data Result Register
104  * - ADC_CV1 - Compare Value Registers
105  * - ADC_CV2 - Compare Value Registers
106  * - ADC_SC2 - Status and Control Register 2
107  * - ADC_SC3 - Status and Control Register 3
108  * - ADC_OFS - ADC Offset Correction Register
109  * - ADC_PG - ADC Plus-Side Gain Register
110  * - ADC_MG - ADC Minus-Side Gain Register
111  * - ADC_CLPD - ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register
112  * - ADC_CLPS - ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register
113  * - ADC_CLP4 - ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register
114  * - ADC_CLP3 - ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register
115  * - ADC_CLP2 - ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register
116  * - ADC_CLP1 - ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register
117  * - ADC_CLP0 - ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register
118  * - ADC_CLMD - ADC Minus-Side General Calibration Value Register
119  * - ADC_CLMS - ADC Minus-Side General Calibration Value Register
120  * - ADC_CLM4 - ADC Minus-Side General Calibration Value Register
121  * - ADC_CLM3 - ADC Minus-Side General Calibration Value Register
122  * - ADC_CLM2 - ADC Minus-Side General Calibration Value Register
123  * - ADC_CLM1 - ADC Minus-Side General Calibration Value Register
124  * - ADC_CLM0 - ADC Minus-Side General Calibration Value Register
125  */
126

128 #define ADC0_IDX (0U)
129 #define ADC1_IDX (1U)
162 #define ADC_RD_SC1(base, index) (ADC_SC1_REG(base, index))
163 #define ADC_WR_SC1(base, index, value) (ADC_SC1_REG(base, index) = (value))
164 #define ADC_RMW_SC1(base, index, mask, value) (ADC_WR_SC1(base, index, (ADC_RD_SC1(base, index) & ~(mask)) | (value)))
165 #define ADC_SET_SC1(base, index, value) (ADC_WR_SC1(base, index, ADC_RD_SC1(base, index) | (value)))
166 #define ADC_CLR_SC1(base, index, value) (ADC_WR_SC1(base, index, ADC_RD_SC1(base, index) & ~(value)))
167 #define ADC_TOG_SC1(base, index, value) (ADC_WR_SC1(base, index, ADC_RD_SC1(base, index) ^ (value)))

2793 #define AIPS_WR_PACRB(base, value) (AIPS_PACRB_REG(base) = (value))
2794 #define AIPS_RMW_PACRB(base, mask, value) (AIPS_WR_PACRB(base, (AIPS_RD_PACRB(base) & ~(mask)) | (value)))
2795 #define AIPS_SET_PACRB(base, value) (AIPS_WR_PACRB(base, AIPS_RD_PACRB(base) | (value)))
2796 #define AIPS_CLR_PACRB(base, value) (AIPS_WR_PACRB(base, AIPS_RD_PACRB(base) & ~(value)))
2797 #define AIPS_TOG_PACRB(base, value) (AIPS_WR_PACRB(base, AIPS_RD_PACRB(base) ^ (value)))

5070 #define AIPS_RMW_PACRF(base, mask, value) (AIPS_WR_PACRF(base, (AIPS_RD_PACRF(base) & ~(mask)) | (value)))

11338  * MK64F12 AXBS
11339  *
11340  * Crossbar switch
11341  *
11342  * Registers defined in this header file:
11343  * - AXBS_PRS - Priority Registers Slave
11344  * - AXBS_CRS - Control Register
11345  * - AXBS_MGPCR0 - Master General Purpose Control Register
11346  * - AXBS_MGPCR1 - Master General Purpose Control Register
11347  * - AXBS_MGPCR2 - Master General Purpose Control Register
11348  * - AXBS_MGPCR3 - Master General Purpose Control Register
11349  * - AXBS_MGPCR4 - Master General Purpose Control Register
11350  * - AXBS_MGPCR5 - Master General Purpose Control Register
11351  */

11388 #define AXBS_CLR_PRS(base, index, value) (AXBS_WR_PRS(base, index, AXBS_RD_PRS(base, index) & ~(value)))

12037 /*
12038  * MK64F12 CAN
12039  *
12040  * Flex Controller Area Network module
12041  *
12042  * Registers defined in this header file:
12043  * - CAN_MCR - Module Configuration Register
12044  * - CAN_CTRL1 - Control 1 register
12045  * - CAN_TIMER - Free Running Timer
12046  * - CAN_RXMGMASK - Rx Mailboxes Global Mask Register
12047  * - CAN_RX14MASK - Rx 14 Mask register
12048  * - CAN_RX15MASK - Rx 15 Mask register
12049  * - CAN_ECR - Error Counter
12050  * - CAN_ESR1 - Error and Status 1 register
12051  * - CAN_IMASK1 - Interrupt Masks 1 register
12052  * - CAN_IFLAG1 - Interrupt Flags 1 register
12053  * - CAN_CTRL2 - Control 2 register
12054  * - CAN_ESR2 - Error and Status 2 register
12055  * - CAN_CRCR - CRC Register
12056  * - CAN_RXFGMASK - Rx FIFO Global Mask register
12057  * - CAN_RXFIR - Rx FIFO Information Register
12058  * - CAN_CS - Message Buffer 0 CS Register
12059  * - CAN_ID - Message Buffer 0 ID Register
12060  * - CAN_WORD0 - Message Buffer 0 WORD0 Register
12061  * - CAN_WORD1 - Message Buffer 0 WORD1 Register
12062  * - CAN_RXIMR - Rx Individual Mask Registers
12063  */
12064 
12065 #define CAN_INSTANCE_COUNT (1U)
12066 #define CAN0_IDX (0U)

12087 #define CAN_SET_MCR(base, value) (CAN_WR_MCR(base, CAN_RD_MCR(base) | (value)))
12088 #define CAN_CLR_MCR(base, value) (CAN_WR_MCR(base, CAN_RD_MCR(base) & ~(value)))
12089 #define CAN_TOG_MCR(base, value) (CAN_WR_MCR(base, CAN_RD_MCR(base) ^ (value)))

14531  * MK64F12 CAU
14532  *
14533  * Memory Mapped Cryptographic Acceleration Unit (MMCAU)
14534  *
14535  * Registers defined in this header file:
14536  * - CAU_DIRECT - Direct access register 0
14537  * - CAU_LDR_CASR - Status register - Load Register command
14538  * - CAU_LDR_CAA - Accumulator register - Load Register command
14539  * - CAU_LDR_CA - General Purpose Register 0 - Load Register command
14540  * - CAU_STR_CASR - Status register - Store Register command
14541  * - CAU_STR_CAA - Accumulator register - Store Register command
14542  * - CAU_STR_CA - General Purpose Register 0 - Store Register command
14543  * - CAU_ADR_CASR - Status register - Add Register command
14544  * - CAU_ADR_CAA - Accumulator register - Add to register command
14545  * - CAU_ADR_CA - General Purpose Register 0 - Add to register command
14546  * - CAU_RADR_CASR - Status register - Reverse and Add to Register command
14547  * - CAU_RADR_CAA - Accumulator register - Reverse and Add to Register command
14548  * - CAU_RADR_CA - General Purpose Register 0 - Reverse and Add to Register command
14549  * - CAU_XOR_CASR - Status register - Exclusive Or command
14550  * - CAU_XOR_CAA - Accumulator register - Exclusive Or command
14551  * - CAU_XOR_CA - General Purpose Register 0 - Exclusive Or command
14552  * - CAU_ROTL_CASR - Status register - Rotate Left command
14553  * - CAU_ROTL_CAA - Accumulator register - Rotate Left command
14554  * - CAU_ROTL_CA - General Purpose Register 0 - Rotate Left command
14555  * - CAU_AESC_CASR - Status register - AES Column Operation command
14556  * - CAU_AESC_CAA - Accumulator register - AES Column Operation command
14557  * - CAU_AESC_CA - General Purpose Register 0 - AES Column Operation command
14558  * - CAU_AESIC_CASR - Status register - AES Inverse Column Operation command
14559  * - CAU_AESIC_CAA - Accumulator register - AES Inverse Column Operation command
14560  * - CAU_AESIC_CA - General Purpose Register 0 - AES Inverse Column Operation command
14561  */

15318 /*
15319  * MK64F12 CMP
15320  *
15321  * High-Speed Comparator (CMP), Voltage Reference (VREF) Digital-to-Analog Converter (DAC), and Analog Mux (ANMUX)
15322  *
15323  * Registers defined in this header file:
15324  * - CMP_CR0 - CMP Control Register 0
15325  * - CMP_CR1 - CMP Control Register 1
15326  * - CMP_FPR - CMP Filter Period Register

16515 /*
16516  * MK64F12 CRC
16517  *
16518  * Cyclic Redundancy Check
16519  *
16520  * Registers defined in this header file:
16521  * - CRC_DATAL - CRC_DATAL register.
16522  * - CRC_DATAH - CRC_DATAH register.
16523  * - CRC_DATALL - CRC_DATALL register.
16524  * - CRC_DATALU - CRC_DATALU register.
16525  * - CRC_DATAHL - CRC_DATAHL register.
16526  * - CRC_DATAHU - CRC_DATAHU register.
16527  * - CRC_DATA - CRC Data register
16528  * - CRC_GPOLY - CRC Polynomial register
16529  * - CRC_GPOLYL - CRC_GPOLYL register.
16530  * - CRC_GPOLYH - CRC_GPOLYH register.
16531  * - CRC_GPOLYLL - CRC_GPOLYLL register.
16532  * - CRC_GPOLYLU - CRC_GPOLYLU register.
16533  * - CRC_GPOLYHL - CRC_GPOLYHL register.
16534  * - CRC_GPOLYHU - CRC_GPOLYHU register.
16535  * - CRC_CTRL - CRC Control register
16536  * - CRC_CTRLHU - CRC_CTRLHU register.
16537  */
16538

16540 #define CRC_IDX (0U)

17713 /*
17714  * MK64F12 DMA
17715  *
17716  * Enhanced direct memory access controller
17717  *
17718  * Registers defined in this header file:
17719  * - DMA_CR - Control Register
17720  * - DMA_ES - Error Status Register
17721  * - DMA_ERQ - Enable Request Register
17722  * - DMA_EEI - Enable Error Interrupt Register
17723  * - DMA_CEEI - Clear Enable Error Interrupt Register
17724  * - DMA_SEEI - Set Enable Error Interrupt Register
17725  * - DMA_CERQ - Clear Enable Request Register
17726  * - DMA_SERQ - Set Enable Request Register
17727  * - DMA_CDNE - Clear DONE Status Bit Register
17728  * - DMA_SSRT - Set START Bit Register
17729  * - DMA_CERR - Clear Error Register
17730  * - DMA_CINT - Clear Interrupt Request Register
17731  * - DMA_INT - Interrupt Request Register
17732  * - DMA_ERR - Error Register
17733  * - DMA_HRS - Hardware Request Status Register
17734  * - DMA_DCHPRI3 - Channel n Priority Register
17735  * - DMA_DCHPRI2 - Channel n Priority Register
17736  * - DMA_DCHPRI1 - Channel n Priority Register
17737  * - DMA_DCHPRI0 - Channel n Priority Register
17738  * - DMA_DCHPRI7 - Channel n Priority Register
17739  * - DMA_DCHPRI6 - Channel n Priority Register
17740  * - DMA_DCHPRI5 - Channel n Priority Register
17741  * - DMA_DCHPRI4 - Channel n Priority Register
17742  * - DMA_DCHPRI11 - Channel n Priority Register
17743  * - DMA_DCHPRI10 - Channel n Priority Register
17744  * - DMA_DCHPRI9 - Channel n Priority Register
17745  * - DMA_DCHPRI8 - Channel n Priority Register
17746  * - DMA_DCHPRI15 - Channel n Priority Register
17747  * - DMA_DCHPRI14 - Channel n Priority Register
17748  * - DMA_DCHPRI13 - Channel n Priority Register
17749  * - DMA_DCHPRI12 - Channel n Priority Register
17750  * - DMA_SADDR - TCD Source Address
17751  * - DMA_SOFF - TCD Signed Source Address Offset
17752  * - DMA_ATTR - TCD Transfer Attributes
17753  * - DMA_NBYTES_MLNO - TCD Minor Byte Count (Minor Loop Disabled)
17754  * - DMA_NBYTES_MLOFFNO - TCD Signed Minor Loop Offset (Minor Loop Enabled and Offset Disabled)
17755  * - DMA_NBYTES_MLOFFYES - TCD Signed Minor Loop Offset (Minor Loop and Offset Enabled)
17756  * - DMA_SLAST - TCD Last Source Address Adjustment
17757  * - DMA_DADDR - TCD Destination Address
17758  * - DMA_DOFF - TCD Signed Destination Address Offset
17759  * - DMA_CITER_ELINKNO - TCD Current Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Disabled)
17760  * - DMA_CITER_ELINKYES - TCD Current Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Enabled)
17761  * - DMA_DLAST_SGA - TCD Last Destination Address Adjustment/Scatter Gather Address
17762  * - DMA_CSR - TCD Control and Status
17763  * - DMA_BITER_ELINKNO - TCD Beginning Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Disabled)
17764  * - DMA_BITER_ELINKYES - TCD Beginning Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Enabled)
17765  */
17766 
17767 #define DMA_INSTANCE_COUNT (1U)
17768 #define DMA_IDX (0U)

28589 /*
28590  * MK64F12 FMC
28591  *
28592  * Flash Memory Controller
28593  *
28594  * Registers defined in this header file:
28595  * - FMC_PFAPR - Flash Access Protection Register
28596  * - FMC_PFB0CR - Flash Bank 0 Control Register
28597  * - FMC_PFB1CR - Flash Bank 1 Control Register
28598  * - FMC_TAGVDW0S - Cache Tag Storage
28599  * - FMC_TAGVDW1S - Cache Tag Storage
28600  * - FMC_TAGVDW2S - Cache Tag Storage
28601  * - FMC_TAGVDW3S - Cache Tag Storage
28602  * - FMC_DATA_U - Cache Data Storage (upper word)
28603  * - FMC_DATA_L - Cache Data Storage (lower word)
28604  */
28605 
28606 #define FMC_INSTANCE_COUNT (1U)
28607 #define FMC_IDX (0U)

29659 /*
29660  * MK64F12 FTFE
29661  *
29662  * Flash Memory Interface
29663  *
29664  * Registers defined in this header file:
29665  * - FTFE_FSTAT - Flash Status Register
29666  * - FTFE_FCNFG - Flash Configuration Register
29667  * - FTFE_FSEC - Flash Security Register
29668  * - FTFE_FOPT - Flash Option Register
29669  * - FTFE_FCCOB3 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29670  * - FTFE_FCCOB2 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29671  * - FTFE_FCCOB1 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29672  * - FTFE_FCCOB0 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29673  * - FTFE_FCCOB7 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29674  * - FTFE_FCCOB6 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29675  * - FTFE_FCCOB5 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29676  * - FTFE_FCCOB4 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29677  * - FTFE_FCCOBB - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29678  * - FTFE_FCCOBA - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29679  * - FTFE_FCCOB9 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29680  * - FTFE_FCCOB8 - Flash Common Command Object Registers
29681  * - FTFE_FPROT3 - Program Flash Protection Registers
29682  * - FTFE_FPROT2 - Program Flash Protection Registers
29683  * - FTFE_FPROT1 - Program Flash Protection Registers
29684  * - FTFE_FPROT0 - Program Flash Protection Registers
29685  * - FTFE_FEPROT - EEPROM Protection Register
29686  * - FTFE_FDPROT - Data Flash Protection Register
29687  */
29688 
29689 #define FTFE_INSTANCE_COUNT (1U)
29690 #define FTFE_IDX (0U)

29716 #define FTFE_CLR_FSTAT(base, value) (FTFE_WR_FSTAT(base, FTFE_RD_FSTAT(base) & ~(value)))
29717 #define FTFE_TOG_FSTAT(base, value) (FTFE_WR_FSTAT(base, FTFE_RD_FSTAT(base) ^ (value)))

30671 /*
30672  * MK64F12 FTM
30673  *
30674  * FlexTimer Module
30675  *
30676  * Registers defined in this header file:
30677  * - FTM_SC - Status And Control
30678  * - FTM_CNT - Counter
30679  * - FTM_MOD - Modulo
30680  * - FTM_CnSC - Channel (n) Status And Control
30681  * - FTM_CnV - Channel (n) Value
30682  * - FTM_CNTIN - Counter Initial Value
30683  * - FTM_STATUS - Capture And Compare Status
30684  * - FTM_MODE - Features Mode Selection
30685  * - FTM_SYNC - Synchronization
30686  * - FTM_OUTINIT - Initial State For Channels Output
30687  * - FTM_OUTMASK - Output Mask
30688  * - FTM_COMBINE - Function For Linked Channels
30689  * - FTM_DEADTIME - Deadtime Insertion Control
30690  * - FTM_EXTTRIG - FTM External Trigger
30691  * - FTM_POL - Channels Polarity
30692  * - FTM_FMS - Fault Mode Status
30693  * - FTM_FILTER - Input Capture Filter Control
30694  * - FTM_FLTCTRL - Fault Control
30695  * - FTM_QDCTRL - Quadrature Decoder Control And Status
30696  * - FTM_CONF - Configuration
30697  * - FTM_FLTPOL - FTM Fault Input Polarity
30698  * - FTM_SYNCONF - Synchronization Configuration

36359 /*
36360  * MK64F12 I2S
36361  *
36362  * Inter-IC Sound / Synchronous Audio Interface
36363  *
36364  * Registers defined in this header file:
36365  * - I2S_TCSR - SAI Transmit Control Register
36366  * - I2S_TCR1 - SAI Transmit Configuration 1 Register
36367  * - I2S_TCR2 - SAI Transmit Configuration 2 Register
36368  * - I2S_TCR3 - SAI Transmit Configuration 3 Register
36369  * - I2S_TCR4 - SAI Transmit Configuration 4 Register
36370  * - I2S_TCR5 - SAI Transmit Configuration 5 Register
36371  * - I2S_TDR - SAI Transmit Data Register
36372  * - I2S_TFR - SAI Transmit FIFO Register
36373  * - I2S_TMR - SAI Transmit Mask Register
36374  * - I2S_RCSR - SAI Receive Control Register
36375  * - I2S_RCR1 - SAI Receive Configuration 1 Register
36376  * - I2S_RCR2 - SAI Receive Configuration 2 Register
36377  * - I2S_RCR3 - SAI Receive Configuration 3 Register
36378  * - I2S_RCR4 - SAI Receive Configuration 4 Register
36379  * - I2S_RCR5 - SAI Receive Configuration 5 Register
36380  * - I2S_RDR - SAI Receive Data Register
36381  * - I2S_RFR - SAI Receive FIFO Register
36382  * - I2S_RMR - SAI Receive Mask Register
36383  * - I2S_MCR - SAI MCLK Control Register
36384  * - I2S_MDR - SAI MCLK Divide Register
36385  */
36386 
36387 #define I2S_INSTANCE_COUNT (1U)
36388 #define I2S0_IDX (0U)

38491  * - LLWU_PE2 - LLWU Pin Enable 2 register

38496  * - LLWU_F2 - LLWU Flag 2 register
38497  * - LLWU_F3 - LLWU Flag 3 register
38498  * - LLWU_FILT1 - LLWU Pin Filter 1 register
38499  * - LLWU_FILT2 - LLWU Pin Filter 2 register

43385 /*
43386  * MK64F12 NV
43387  *
43388  * Flash configuration field
43389  *
43390  * Registers defined in this header file:
43391  * - NV_BACKKEY3 - Backdoor Comparison Key 3.
43392  * - NV_BACKKEY2 - Backdoor Comparison Key 2.
43393  * - NV_BACKKEY1 - Backdoor Comparison Key 1.
43394  * - NV_BACKKEY0 - Backdoor Comparison Key 0.
43395  * - NV_BACKKEY7 - Backdoor Comparison Key 7.
43396  * - NV_BACKKEY6 - Backdoor Comparison Key 6.
43397  * - NV_BACKKEY5 - Backdoor Comparison Key 5.
43398  * - NV_BACKKEY4 - Backdoor Comparison Key 4.
43399  * - NV_FPROT3 - Non-volatile P-Flash Protection 1 - Low Register
43400  * - NV_FPROT2 - Non-volatile P-Flash Protection 1 - High Register
43401  * - NV_FPROT1 - Non-volatile P-Flash Protection 0 - Low Register
43402  * - NV_FPROT0 - Non-volatile P-Flash Protection 0 - High Register
43403  * - NV_FSEC - Non-volatile Flash Security Register
43404  * - NV_FOPT - Non-volatile Flash Option Register
43405  * - NV_FEPROT - Non-volatile EERAM Protection Register
43406  * - NV_FDPROT - Non-volatile D-Flash Protection Register
43407  */
43408 
43409 #define NV_INSTANCE_COUNT (1U)
43410 #define FTFE_FlashConfig_IDX (0U)

48022 /*
48023  * MK64F12 SDHC
48024  *
48025  * Secured Digital Host Controller
48026  *
48027  * Registers defined in this header file:
48028  * - SDHC_DSADDR - DMA System Address register
48029  * - SDHC_BLKATTR - Block Attributes register
48030  * - SDHC_CMDARG - Command Argument register
48031  * - SDHC_XFERTYP - Transfer Type register
48032  * - SDHC_CMDRSP - Command Response 0
48033  * - SDHC_DATPORT - Buffer Data Port register
48034  * - SDHC_PRSSTAT - Present State register
48035  * - SDHC_PROCTL - Protocol Control register
48036  * - SDHC_SYSCTL - System Control register
48037  * - SDHC_IRQSTAT - Interrupt Status register
48038  * - SDHC_IRQSTATEN - Interrupt Status Enable register
48039  * - SDHC_IRQSIGEN - Interrupt Signal Enable register
48040  * - SDHC_AC12ERR - Auto CMD12 Error Status Register
48041  * - SDHC_HTCAPBLT - Host Controller Capabilities
48042  * - SDHC_WML - Watermark Level Register
48043  * - SDHC_FEVT - Force Event register
48044  * - SDHC_ADMAES - ADMA Error Status register
48045  * - SDHC_ADSADDR - ADMA System Addressregister
48046  * - SDHC_VENDOR - Vendor Specific register
48047  * - SDHC_MMCBOOT - MMC Boot register
48048  * - SDHC_HOSTVER - Host Controller Version
48049  */
48050 
48051 #define SDHC_INSTANCE_COUNT (1U)
48052 #define SDHC_IDX (0U)

51704 /*
51705  * MK64F12 SIM
51706  *
51707  * System Integration Module
51708  *
51709  * Registers defined in this header file:
51710  * - SIM_SOPT1 - System Options Register 1
51711  * - SIM_SOPT1CFG - SOPT1 Configuration Register
51712  * - SIM_SOPT2 - System Options Register 2
51713  * - SIM_SOPT4 - System Options Register 4
51714  * - SIM_SOPT5 - System Options Register 5
51715  * - SIM_SOPT7 - System Options Register 7
51716  * - SIM_SDID - System Device Identification Register
51717  * - SIM_SCGC1 - System Clock Gating Control Register 1
51718  * - SIM_SCGC2 - System Clock Gating Control Register 2
51719  * - SIM_SCGC3 - System Clock Gating Control Register 3
51720  * - SIM_SCGC4 - System Clock Gating Control Register 4
51721  * - SIM_SCGC5 - System Clock Gating Control Register 5
51722  * - SIM_SCGC6 - System Clock Gating Control Register 6
51723  * - SIM_SCGC7 - System Clock Gating Control Register 7
51724  * - SIM_CLKDIV1 - System Clock Divider Register 1
51725  * - SIM_CLKDIV2 - System Clock Divider Register 2
51726  * - SIM_FCFG1 - Flash Configuration Register 1
51727  * - SIM_FCFG2 - Flash Configuration Register 2
51728  * - SIM_UIDH - Unique Identification Register High
51729  * - SIM_UIDMH - Unique Identification Register Mid-High
51730  * - SIM_UIDML - Unique Identification Register Mid Low
51731  * - SIM_UIDL - Unique Identification Register Low
51732  */

53010 #define SIM_WR_SCGC_BIT(base, index, value) (SIM_SCGC_BIT_REG((base), (index)) = (SIM_SCGC_BIT_REG((base), (index)) & ~(1U << SIM_SCGC_BIT_SHIFT(index))) | ((uint32_t)(value) << SIM_SCGC_BIT_SHIFT(index)))
53011 #define SIM_BWR_SCGC_BIT(base, index, value) (BITBAND_ACCESS32(&SIM_SCGC_BIT_REG((base), (index)), SIM_SCGC_BIT_SHIFT(index)) = (uint32_t)(value))

54981 /*
54982  * MK64F12 SPI
54983  *
54984  * Serial Peripheral Interface
54985  *
54986  * Registers defined in this header file:
54987  * - SPI_MCR - Module Configuration Register
54988  * - SPI_TCR - Transfer Count Register
54989  * - SPI_CTAR - Clock and Transfer Attributes Register (In Master Mode)
54990  * - SPI_CTAR_SLAVE - Clock and Transfer Attributes Register (In Slave Mode)
54991  * - SPI_SR - Status Register
54992  * - SPI_RSER - DMA/Interrupt Request Select and Enable Register
54993  * - SPI_PUSHR - PUSH TX FIFO Register In Master Mode
54994  * - SPI_PUSHR_SLAVE - PUSH TX FIFO Register In Slave Mode
54995  * - SPI_POPR - POP RX FIFO Register
54996  * - SPI_TXFR0 - Transmit FIFO Registers
54997  * - SPI_TXFR1 - Transmit FIFO Registers
54998  * - SPI_TXFR2 - Transmit FIFO Registers
54999  * - SPI_TXFR3 - Transmit FIFO Registers
55000  * - SPI_RXFR0 - Receive FIFO Registers
55001  * - SPI_RXFR1 - Receive FIFO Registers
55002  * - SPI_RXFR2 - Receive FIFO Registers
55003  * - SPI_RXFR3 - Receive FIFO Registers
55004  */
55005 
55006 #define SPI_INSTANCE_COUNT (3U)
55007 #define SPI0_IDX (0U)
55008 #define SPI1_IDX (1U)
55009 #define SPI2_IDX (2U)

55033 #define SPI_CLR_MCR(base, value) (SPI_WR_MCR(base, SPI_RD_MCR(base) & ~(value)))
55034 #define SPI_TOG_MCR(base, value) (SPI_WR_MCR(base, SPI_RD_MCR(base) ^ (value)))

56724 /*
56725  * MK64F12 UART
56726  *
56727  * Serial Communication Interface
56728  *
56729  * Registers defined in this header file:
56730  * - UART_BDH - UART Baud Rate Registers: High
56731  * - UART_BDL - UART Baud Rate Registers: Low
56732  * - UART_C1 - UART Control Register 1
56733  * - UART_C2 - UART Control Register 2
56734  * - UART_S1 - UART Status Register 1
56735  * - UART_S2 - UART Status Register 2
56736  * - UART_C3 - UART Control Register 3
56737  * - UART_D - UART Data Register
56738  * - UART_MA1 - UART Match Address Registers 1
56739  * - UART_MA2 - UART Match Address Registers 2
56740  * - UART_C4 - UART Control Register 4
56741  * - UART_C5 - UART Control Register 5
56742  * - UART_ED - UART Extended Data Register
56743  * - UART_MODEM - UART Modem Register
56744  * - UART_IR - UART Infrared Register
56745  * - UART_PFIFO - UART FIFO Parameters
56746  * - UART_CFIFO - UART FIFO Control Register
56747  * - UART_SFIFO - UART FIFO Status Register
56748  * - UART_TWFIFO - UART FIFO Transmit Watermark
56749  * - UART_TCFIFO - UART FIFO Transmit Count
56750  * - UART_RWFIFO - UART FIFO Receive Watermark
56751  * - UART_RCFIFO - UART FIFO Receive Count
56752  * - UART_C7816 - UART 7816 Control Register
56753  * - UART_IE7816 - UART 7816 Interrupt Enable Register
56754  * - UART_IS7816 - UART 7816 Interrupt Status Register
56755  * - UART_WP7816T0 - UART 7816 Wait Parameter Register
56756  * - UART_WP7816T1 - UART 7816 Wait Parameter Register
56757  * - UART_WN7816 - UART 7816 Wait N Register
56758  * - UART_WF7816 - UART 7816 Wait FD Register
56759  * - UART_ET7816 - UART 7816 Error Threshold Register
56760  * - UART_TL7816 - UART 7816 Transmit Length Register
56761  */
56762 
56763 #define UART_INSTANCE_COUNT (6U)
56764 #define UART0_IDX (0U)
56765 #define UART1_IDX (1U)
56766 #define UART2_IDX (2U)
56767 #define UART3_IDX (3U)
56768 #define UART4_IDX (4U)
56769 #define UART5_IDX (5U)

59805 /*
59806  * MK64F12 USB
59807  *
59808  * Universal Serial Bus, OTG Capable Controller
59809  *
59810  * Registers defined in this header file:
59811  * - USB_PERID - Peripheral ID register
59812  * - USB_IDCOMP - Peripheral ID Complement register
59813  * - USB_REV - Peripheral Revision register
59814  * - USB_ADDINFO - Peripheral Additional Info register
59815  * - USB_OTGISTAT - OTG Interrupt Status register
59816  * - USB_OTGICR - OTG Interrupt Control register
59817  * - USB_OTGSTAT - OTG Status register
59818  * - USB_OTGCTL - OTG Control register
59819  * - USB_ISTAT - Interrupt Status register
59820  * - USB_INTEN - Interrupt Enable register
59821  * - USB_ERRSTAT - Error Interrupt Status register
59822  * - USB_ERREN - Error Interrupt Enable register
59823  * - USB_STAT - Status register
59824  * - USB_CTL - Control register
59825  * - USB_ADDR - Address register
59826  * - USB_BDTPAGE1 - BDT Page register 1
59827  * - USB_FRMNUML - Frame Number register Low
59828  * - USB_FRMNUMH - Frame Number register High
59829  * - USB_TOKEN - Token register
59830  * - USB_SOFTHLD - SOF Threshold register
59831  * - USB_BDTPAGE2 - BDT Page Register 2
59832  * - USB_BDTPAGE3 - BDT Page Register 3
59833  * - USB_ENDPT - Endpoint Control register
59834  * - USB_USBCTRL - USB Control register
59835  * - USB_OBSERVE - USB OTG Observe register
59836  * - USB_CONTROL - USB OTG Control register
59837  * - USB_USBTRC0 - USB Transceiver Control register 0
59838  * - USB_USBFRMADJUST - Frame Adjust Register
59839  * - USB_CLK_RECOVER_CTRL - USB Clock recovery control
59840  * - USB_CLK_RECOVER_IRC_EN - IRC48M oscillator enable register
59841  * - USB_CLK_RECOVER_INT_STATUS - Clock recovery separated interrupt status
59842  */
59843 
59844 #define USB_INSTANCE_COUNT (1U)
59845 #define USB0_IDX (0U)
59862 #define USB_RD_PERID(base) (USB_PERID_REG(base))
